'''Mass gatherings''' are events attended by a sufficient number of people to strain the planning and response resources of the host community, state/province, nation, or region where it is being held.<ref name="one">{{citation | title = 4º Encontro da Rede CIEVS (Centro de Informação em Saúde para Viajantes)
|trans-title=Brazil- Conference: The 4th Annual Meeting of the CIEVS network| work = Mass Gathering Guidelines= OEI
| date = 2010-10-28
| accessdate = 2010-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ranse|first=Jamie|last2=Hutton|first2=Alison|date=December 2012|title=Minimum Data Set for Mass-Gathering Health Research and Evaluation: A Discussion Paper|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/prehospital-and-disaster-medicine/article/minimum-data-set-for-massgathering-health-research-and-evaluation-a-discussion-paper/3952C33AB6933EA30923CB2D436173CC|journal=Prehospital and Disaster Medicine|language=en|volume=27|issue=6|pages=543–550|doi=10.1017/s1049023x12001288|issn=1049-023X}}</ref>    Definitions of a mass gathering generally include the following:
* Planned (long term or spontaneously planned) event
* “a specified number of persons (at least >1000 persons)
* at a specific location, for a specific purpose (e.g. [[social function]], public event, [[sporting event]]) for a defined period of time”.
* Requires Multi-Agency Coordination

[[Mass Gathering Medicine]]  is  a new field of [[medicine]] that focuses on the health risks of mass gatherings.<ref>{{cite web|title=Public Health Preparedness for Mass Gatherings |url=http://sis.nlm.nih.gov/enviro/massgatherings.html#a0 | accessdate =2010-11-04}}</ref>   The [[World Health Organization]] through its "Department of Global Alert and Response" supports Member States hosting mass gatherings and regularly receives a large number of requests for [[technical support]] by countries organizing large mass gatherings.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mass Gatherings and Public Health|url=http://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/98415/E90712.pdf|year=2007| accessdate =2010-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Communicable disease alert and response for mass gatherings|url=http://www.who.int/csr/Mass_gatherings2.pdf | accessdate =2010-11-04}}</ref>

