{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox officeholder |name = Nasir Khan Durrani (PSP) |honorific-prefix = Inspector General of Police (IGP) |honorific-suffix = |native_name = ناصر خان درانی |native_name_lang = [[Urdu]] |image =[http://kppolice.gov.pk/images/igp.jpg] |caption =Nasir Khan Durrani |governor1 = [[Mehtab Ahmed Khan Abbasi|Mehtab Ahmed Khan]] [[Iqbal Zafar Jhagra]] |office1 = [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Police|Inspector General of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Police]] |predecessor1 = [[National Counter Terrorism Authority|Lt. Cdr (R) Ihsan Ghani]] |successor1 = [[Salahuddin Khan Mehsud]] |alma_mater = |nickname = |allegiance = {{PAK}} |branch = [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Police]] & [[Punjab Police (Pakistan)|Punjab Police]] |serviceyears = |rank = [[Inspector General]] |unit = |commands = |battles = |term_start1 = 25 September 2013 |term_end1 = 16 March 2017 |awards |ethnicity = Punjabi <ref name="auto">{{cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1186032 |title=Promotion dilemma of bureaucracy|publisher=[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]] |date=2015-06-04 |accessdate=2015-06-05}}</ref> }}
'''Nasir Durrani''' is a retired [[Pakistani]] police officer who served in [[Grade 22|BPS-22 grade]]. Durrani is highly regarded as an honest police officer in the country and currently serves as [[Punjab Police (Pakistan)|Chairman Punjab Police Reform Commission]]. In September 2013, he was appointed as the Provincial Police Office ([[Inspector General of Police]]) of the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] thus making him top cop of the province, where he served till March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/amp/1320870|title=Nasir Khan Durrani relinquishes charge as Khyber Pakhtunkhwa IG|first=Ali|last=Akbar|date=16 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> As Inspector General of Police, Durrani oversaw all patrol and speciality units, and managed department policy that affected Khyber Pakhtunkhwa's many diverse communities.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1044845/nasir-durrani-appointed-as-new-ig-of-kp-police |title=Nasir Durrani appointed as new IG of KP police |publisher=[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]] |date=2013-09-23 |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref> He is a [[Pathans of Punjab|Pathan of Punjab]], belonging to [[Durrani]] tribe.<ref name="auto"/>
Durrani's tenure as chief of [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Police]] earned him fame and good repute since his policies were admired by the public. Showing his intellect, he managed to establish police specialised schools all over the province which has a vital part to play in raising the standards of policing. He is also credited as a pioneer of the safe city and rapid response projects of KPK police.
After winning the elections in 2018, [[Imran Khan]] shared in his first speech to the nation that he has asked Durrani to help improve the police standards of Punjab province. He was subsequently appointed as the chairman of the [[Punjab Police (Pakistan)|Punjab Police Reform Commission]] in September 2018.<ref>https://www.thenews.com.pk/amp/361811-nasir-durrani-to-head-punjab-police-reform-commission</ref>
